Veganism isnt a diet. Definition of “veganism” as: 
"A philosophy and way of living which seeks to exclude—as far as is possible and practicable—all forms of exploitation of, and cruelty to, animals for food, clothing or any other purpose; and by extension, promotes the development and use of animal-free alternatives for the benefit of humans, animals and the environment. In dietary terms it denotes the practice of dispensing with all products derived wholly or partly from animals."
A plant based diet is a diet.

Rich greens spirilina r not good sources of b12 if not fortified. A supplement or maybe duckweed if it has enuf b12 r how to get b12. U can also eat fortified foods but a supplement is probly easier.

Gov recomends people eat as little cholesterol as possible while still getting adequate nutrient intake. Cholesterol is only found in animal products. Dietary Saturated fat intake is not needed and to much is unhealthy. Saturated fat is often higher in animal products.
To much sat fat and cholesterol intake is a leading cause of death.
Watch uprooting the leading causes of death.

Gov says a healthy vegan diet is healthiest. Plant based food is ready to be used by the body.
Its better to get your nutrients from a plant based diet cuz it often doesnt come with the bad things found in animal products.
A proper vegan or plant based diet is healthiest for humans.

The blood test chick is dumb.
Supplements can be part of your diet.

Watch earthlings the movie it's free on youtube.

snippet.textDisplay: I kindof dont have the ability to go vegan though :( . Sadly for me, I have Ulcerative colitis and it gets inflamed with foods that dont digest well. And tons of nuts, beans, seeds, and tough veggies cause massive damage to the ulcers and inflammation which leads to horrible pain. But I can say without a doubt Soda is one of the worst things you can put in yourself. It is what caused my ulcerative colitis, and it can do much much worse. And it's crazy to see how many people drink multiple sodas a day without a second thought. I heard an interesting fact once that always stuck with me when changing diets and learning more about my condition. "There is a reason cops carry a 2L of coke in the trunk of the car. It is used to clean the blood off the roads and sidewalks after any gruesome event. It's that acidic."

snippet.textDisplay: Dude, your results were not ‘shockingly good’. Having a bit lower thyroid might even be good for longevity. Having a bit lower testosterone might be good for longevity. Seems like you’ve decreased your HDL (I assume that’s what she meant?), so overall potentially worse than before. But honestly, you should have published all the results, not some cherry-picked ones from the doctor. What about triglycerides? What about you DHA status? What about zinc? What about Retinol? What about LDL or ApoB? What about all other Vitamins and minerals? What about omega 3 to omega 6 ratio? What about inflammation markers? What about hba1c?
